    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Eugenicists relied heavily on flawed scientific theories, such as Social Darwinism, to justify their views on racial hierarchies. They believed that certain groups, typically those with \"desirable\" traits like intelligence, physical strength, and European features, were superior to others, citing pseudo-scientific concepts like \"heredity\" and \"racial purity.\" They also pointed to supposed correlations between crime rates, poverty, and \"inferior\" racial groups, arguing that these factors were evidence of inherent inferiority. Furthermore, eugenicists often cited outdated and discredited theories, such as the idea that \"non-white\" skin was a sign of inferiority.",
