      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Eugenicists employed various methods, including IQ testing and craniometry, to supposedly prove the hereditary differences between groups. They claimed that IQ tests, such as those developed by Alfred Binet, measured innate intelligence, which was seen as a product of hereditary factors. They argued that Northern Europeans scored higher on these tests, indicating a higher level of intelligence and evolutionary advancement. Craniometry, the study of skull shapes and sizes, was used to measure cranial capacity, with the assumption that larger skulls were indicative of greater intelligence and evolutionary superiority. They also pointed to supposed correlations between skull size and other physical characteristics, such as nose shape and skin color, as evidence of hereditary differences between groups. Furthermore, they often cited outdated and discredited theories, such as the idea that the \"Negroid\" skull was smaller and more primitive than the \"Caucasian\" skull, to justify their claims.",
      "source": "target",
